I had a project with build problems:

"The type (...) cannot be resolved. It is indirectly referenced from required
.class files."

Opening the Java editor (by double-clicking the problem marker or the file in
the package explorer) for the problematic class caused a "Internal Error" dialog
to appear. My log contained exceptions like the one below. I could repeat it as
many times as I wanted. But after I fixed the project classpath, it stopped
happening. Forcing the classpath to be wrong did not allow me to reproduce the
problem.
